title: A Surprising WTA Finals Victory Mirrors the Year in Women’s Tennis
description: Caroline Garcia, ranked just 79th in May, won the season-ending championship and will finish at No. 4 in a year that saw Serena Williams and Ashleigh Barty retire.
dc:creator: Christopher Clarey
media:description: Caroline Garcia of France after defeating Aryna Sabalenka of Belarus to win the WTA Finals women’s singles final.
